717715f-a.text:

715227f-a.title: Manhattan: 120th Street (West) - Broadway
715227f-a.text:
West 120th Street, south side, west from and including Broadway to Claremont Ave., showing the Barnard College Building, which contains Brinckerhoff, Milbank and Fiske Halls. This building occupies the complete block between 119th and 120th Streets, between the afore mentioned Aves. and bears No. 3025 on Broadway, which side is largely shown.
1936.
Walter L. Bogert.

717713f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 120th Street (West)
717713f-a.text:
Broadway, at Aest 120th Street, showing in the foreground (S.W. corner), the Athletic Field of Barnard College. Aoross West 120th Street and partially hidden by trees, are three units, Fiske, Millbank and Brinkerhoff Halls, of the College. The latter is at the N.W. corner of the afore mentioned streets. Across its roof, aopears the tower of the Addnistration and Library Buildings of the Union Theological Seminary. The large tower shown on the left, is that of the Riverside Baptist Church, which is located on Riverside
Drive, at the S.E. corner of West 122nd Street.
1936.
Walter L. Bogert.
